SleepTwentySecsCommand¶

robot.commands.sleep.SleepTwentySecsCommand.SleepTwentySecsCommand

class SleepTwentySecsCommand[source]¶

Bases: CommandInterface

Methods

execute

Start a thread to sleep twenty seconds before responding.

sleepTwenty

This method will wait for 20 seconds before sending a response.
execute(responseStatusCallback, jsonObject)[source]¶

Start a thread to sleep twenty seconds before responding.

Parameters:

  • responseStatusCallback (func) – A callback function has to be passed, that will send status of command execution back to the controller. This callback will be passed by the caller of execute().

  • jsonObject (dictionary) – A JSON object initially containing the command json, modified to include response information.

sleepTwenty(responseStatusCallback, jsonObject)[source]¶

This method will wait for 20 seconds before sending a response.

Parameters:

  • responseStatusCallback (func) – A callback function has to be passed, that will send status of command execution back to the controller. This callback will be passed by the caller of execute().

  • jsonObject (dictionary) – A JSON object initially containing the command json, modified to include response information.
